Academic critique	Too intensive — judges become policy-makers (Lord Sumption, Tigere)	Too deferential — no structured analysis, opaque (Lord Kerr, Keyu)
Post-Brexit position?	Retained in HRA cases; EU law no longer mandates it in domestic courts	Retained; question of whether proportionality will expand post-Brexit remains open


